snippet.textDisplay: Have seen dozens of covers of this song and you are the only one to actually sing the full dynamic range (or at least very very close to it) of the original.  I like the way you made it your own without removing the magic of the original, and every instrument player was spot-on.  The subtle changes worked well, and I could tell you all cared about the song you were playing.  As Beethoven said, â€œTo play a wrong note is insignificant.  To play without passion is inexcusable!â€  You guys really didnâ€™t do either, but after watching a plethora of covers treat this song like ink on a paper, it was magnificent and absolutely beautiful.
